import numpy as np
import random
from scipy import stats
np.random.seed(0)

target_materials = ['plastic', 'aluminium', 'polypropylene', 'gold']
pulse_widths = list(range(24, 13001))
energies = np.linspace(min([v for v in [6.83e+19, 1.55, 2.31, 10, 2.41]) # Ensuring pulse widths are within given range
spot_sizes = list(np.arange(2.13, 60.1, step=0.1))
intensities = np.linspace(min([v for v in [5.09e+18, 4.53e+19]), max([v for v in [6.59e+20]]), num=10)
powers = list(np.arange(1.76e+11, 3.83e+14, step=1)) # Ensuring powers are within given range
cutoff_energies = np.linspace(min([v for v in [4.0, 4.4, 6.2]]), max([v for v in [95]]), num=8)
np.random.seed(1) # Set seed for reproducibility
generated_data = []
for _ in range(25):
    target_material = random.choice(target_materials)
    pulse_width = np.random.choice(pulse_widths, p=[v/sum(pulse_widths) for v in pulse_widths]) # Ensuring distribution according to given statistics
    energy = np.random.choice(energies, p=np.diff([min(energies), max(energies)]*len(energies)) + min(energies) 
    spot_size = np.random.choice(spot_sizes, p=[v/sum(spot_sizes) for v in spot_sizes]) # Ensuring distribution according to given statistics
    intensity = np.random.choice(intensities, p=np.diff([min(intensities), max(intensities)]*len(intensities)) + min(intensities) 
    power = np.random.choice(powers, p=[v/sum(powers) for v in powers]) # Ensuring distribution according to given statistics
    cutoff_energy = np.random.choice(cutoff_energies, p=np.diff([min(cutoff_energies), max(cutoff_energies)]*len(cutoff_energies)) + min(cutoff_energies) 
    generated_data.append([target_material, pulse_width, energy, spot_size, intensity, power, cutoff_energy])
generated_data = np.array(generated_data)
print(generated_data)
```
